    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-01T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="469"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.1153 Feiting/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-01T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 1, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 1—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1054. My 1048, November 30, 9 p.m. The launch has been returned by the Japanese
                    with the flag restored. The written report made to <pb facs="0395" n="387"
                        xml:id="pg_387"/> me by the American company states that the Japanese
                    sailors lowered the American flag and tossed it to the crew of an adjacent
                    launch. The details required by your 593, November 30, 7 p.m. will follow
                        later.<note n="21" xml:id="d469fn21">Telegram No. 1055, December 1, 5 p.m.,
                        not printed. The Consul General reported that after careful investigation he
                        considered that the sale of the launch to the American company was made in
                        good faith. (394.1153 Feiting/6)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
